videos.description: Isaac Hamilton feeds a leading Ike Anigbogu to connect on an and-1 against Oregon.
videos.headline: UCLA's Ike Anigbogu connects on and-1

videos.description: Payton Pritchard feeds Chris Boucher down low for the slam and a seven-point Oregon lead over UCLA.

tracking.trackingName: NCB_One-Play (Beautiful pass sets up Oregon's Boucher for slam) 2016/12/28 ESHEET

videos.headline: Pritchard sets up Boucher for Oregon slam

videos.description: 2H (16:34) ORE Jordan Bell made Three Point Jumper. Assisted by Tyler Dorsey.
videos.headline: Jordan Bell connects on just his third three pointer of the season as the shot clock winds down

videos.description: Lonzo Ball is taking over the game, draining a 3-pointer while getting knocked down and putting UCLA up 70-65.
videos.headline: Ball knocked down as he drains the 3

videos.description: 2H (6:50) UCLA Bryce Alford made Three Point Jumper. Assisted by TJ Leaf.
videos.headline: Great UCLA ball movement sets up Bryce Alford to drain a three

videos.description: 2H (4:55) ORE Jordan Bell made Dunk. Assisted by Dylan Ennis.
videos.headline: #SCTop10 moment as Oregon tosses a long alley oop to Jordan Bell in transition

videos.description: 2H (0:15) ORE Payton Pritchard made Three Point Jumper. Assisted by Dillon Brooks.
videos.headline: Payton Pritchard bangs a three to bring Oregon within 1 with 12 seconds left

videos.description: 2H (0:01) ORE Dillon Brooks made Three Point Jumper. Assisted by Payton Pritchard.
videos.headline: Dillon Brooks hits a three with less than a second left to give Oregon a 2 point lead

videos.description: Oregon's Dillon Brooks joins Kevin Connors on SportsCenter to break down the play leading to his game-winning 3-pointer against No. 2 UCLA and the thoughts in his mind when the shot went in.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCB Interview (Oregon's Brooks says beating UCLA feels amazing) 2016/12/28 ESHEET SC

videos.headline: Oregon's Brooks says beating UCLA feels amazing

videos.description: Despite a late surge from UCLA, with Lonzo Ball scoring 14 points and dishing out six assists, Dillon Brooks sinks the game winner as part of a 23-point night in the Ducks' 89-87  upset of the Bruins.
videos.headline: Brooks lifts Oregon past No. 2 UCLA
